sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K392036
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: endoglucanase/CBM secretion testing construct for yeast
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Yeast expression device containing C. fermi endoglucanase CenA fused with cellulose-binding motif CM10; engineered secretion tag attached upstream to enable secretion of fusion protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Assembled from Silver standard-compatible parts. Sequence shown on part's main page may not be accurate since it assumes Standard assembly. Please check sequencing results from Get This Part page instead.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Teoh Shao Thing, Rie Takino, Kosuke Torigata

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K416003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was sent to use from Dr. Sheldon Park of the University of Buffalo.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This secretion tag when linked to the N-terminal of the protein directs extracellular secretion of the protein. After targeting through the ER to the golgi, this "pre-pro" tag is cleaved by the KEX-2 protease resulting in secretion of protein without the aforementioned tag. To use this tag, attached it directly upstream of your proteins CDS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There was an illegal Xbal1 site at bp 101 and we removed it through altering the primers necessary for biobricking the sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Phair

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K105027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the core of the CYC1 promoter of ''S. cerevisiae''. This promoter element allows basal transcription. The transcription signal can be modulated by adding operator sites upstream of this BioBrick. In that way activators or repressors can act on the transcription machinery.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This BioBrick contains the TATA-box and most of the 5'UTR (-139 to -36, relative to the translational start)of the natural CYC1 promoter. A Kozak sequence is not included and has thus to be added!
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Wild

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: consensus Kozak sequence and start codon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: designed such that fusion using fusion bricks assembly method leads to in frame translation
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caroline Ajo-Franklin
